 1990s radio show called Kaybedenler Kulübü (Losers' Club), struggle to deal with their daily lives after their show becomes an instant hit. Kaan meets Zeynep, the girl of his dreams, but their relationship comes under pressure as the show continues to stir controversy and attract fans from every segment of Istanbul society.","genre_ids":[35,18],"media_type":"movie","popularity":1.2566,"vote_count":145,"poster_path":"/kTffzdbvp8EXZ602qZGlB6yWfWt.jpg","release_date":"2011-03-25","vote_average":6.528,"backdrop_path":"/ktGl5QUiQUiWjlccUuqvkZWDWGL.jpg","original_title":"Kaybedenler Kulübü","original_language":"tr"}],"similar_content":[{"id":247193,"adult":false,"title":"Bajo un manto de estrellas","video":false,"overview":"","genre_ids":[18,36],"popularity":0.1177,"vote_count":3,"poster_path":"/8UHtaaZUIr6ZVWHKQpBW9PL92Ak.jpg","release_date":"2014-02-14","vote_average":6.7,"backdrop_path":null,"original_title":"Bajo un manto de estrellas","original_language":"es"},{"id":205,"adult":false,"title":"Hotel Rwanda","video":false,"overview":"Inspired by true events, this film takes place in Rwanda in the 1990s when more than a million Tutsis were killed in a genocide that went mostly unnoticed by the rest of the world. Hotel owner Paul Rusesabagina houses over a thousand refuges in his hotel in attempt to save their lives.","genre_ids":[18,36,10752],"popularity":3.4816,"vote_count":3090,"poster_path":"/p3pHw85UMZPegfMZBA6dZ06yarm.jpg","release_date":"2004-12-22","vote_average":7.7,"backdrop_path":"/jkvvXaN7FPVKGlk8oj9PL0FHNtj.jpg","original_title":"Hotel Rwanda","original_language":"en"},{"id":207,"adult":false,"title":"Dead Poets Society","video":false,"overview":"At an elite, old-fashioned boarding school in New England, a passionate English teacher inspires his students to rebel against convention and seize the potential of every day, courting the disdain of the stern headmaster.","genre_ids":[18],"popularity":11.8108,"vote_count":12309,"poster_path":"/l5NbiHKUmahlAT3Q1ig8